    "headline": "Gold Drops 7%. Why It Is Losing Out to Higher Oil Prices and Interest Rates.",
    "summary": "The price of gold dropped early Thursday, as heightened tensions in the Middle East drove oil prices higher and dimmed the prospects of a near-term rate cut by the Federal Reserve.  Continuous gold futures  plunged 6.7% to $4,560.10 an ounce, falling $309 from its intraday high.  Precious metal mining stocks also dropped –  Freeport-McMoRan Newmont  and  Royal Gold  fell ahead of the bell – by 4.4%, 7.6%, and 4.6%, respectively.",
