    "headline": "Gold Drops 6%. Why It Is Losing Out to Higher Oil Prices and Interest Rates.",
    "summary": "The price of gold tumbled on Thursday as flaring tensions in the Middle East drove oil prices higher and dimmed the prospects of a near-term rate cut by the Federal Reserve.  Silver futures  fared even worse, falling 8.2% to $71.22 on Thursday.  Elsewhere,  Brent crude futures  the international benchmark, settled up 1.2% at $108.65 after Iran struck key energy infrastructure across the Middle East overnight.",
